Write Met-Station image to SD card using Etcher 
https://etcher.io/

Safely remove SD card, put into Raspberry Pi and power on. 

Login locally or over ssh (weewx - none)

Resize partitions to fill SD card
sudo raspi-config
Advanced -> Expand Filesystem -> Reboot

Edit station info
sudo nano ~/system37/weewx.conf

Make edits in the information section, these should be specific to the station to be assigned: 

[Station]

    # Description of the station location
    location = Weather Station 001

    # Latitude and longitude in decimal degrees
    latitude = 50.11
    longitude = -5.275

    # Altitude of the station, with unit it is in. 
    altitude = 100, meter    # Choose 'foot' or 'meter' for unit

Save and exit (Ctrl-X) -> 'Y'

Restart weewx service
sudo service weewx restart

Setup Ambient weather metstation:

Upgrade to firmware 2.2.7
Firmware - http://www.aercusinstruments.com/content/downloads/WH2600_V2.2.7.bin
Tool - http://www.aercusinstruments.com/content/downloads/IP%20Tools%2832bit%29.exe

Open web interface

Configure Local Network - Local Device Network Settings
IP Address - Static
Static IP Address - 192.168.0.200
Static subnet mask - 255.255.255.0
Static default gateway - 192.168.0.1
Static DNS server - 192.168.0.1
Server listening port - 5000
->Apply

Weather network - Weather Station Settings
Remote Server - Customized
Server IP - 192.168.0.201
Server Port - 8080
Server Type - PHP
Station ID - 0000 (use unique ID number 001 - 025)
Password - none
->Apply

Check live data is coming from remote sensors
Wait 5 minutes then check weex server:
http://192.168.0.201/weewx
